'''Level 4.4''', or '''Intrusive Configuration''', is the fourth sub-level of [[Level 4]]. This level is widely infamous for its bizarre mind-controlling properties and highly unsettling atmosphere, justifying the need for an immediate exit upon entering.
==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=crazed state ahhhh.webp|caption=An image of Level 4.4.}}
{{Blurimage|file=bloodied bathroom.jpg|caption=Another image of Level 4.4. Photographer was confirmed to have been decapitated.}}
{{Blurimage|file=halloween cosplay smh.jpg|caption=A body bag found in Level 4.4, along with several organs surrounding it. Photo censored in accordance with database publishing guidelines.}}

'''Level 4.4''' resembles a large complex of indeterminable size, with its architecture being comparable to that of a typical office building. The level itself does not contain any artificial light sources, instead being lit up through unknown means. The defining feature of '''Level 4.4''' that sets it apart from [[Level 4]] is the gory, dilapidated appearance of several hallways and areas. While wandering through '''Level 4.4''', the stench of rotten flesh could be felt within the air, causing severe feelings of dread and anxiety. In extreme cases, these can lead to sudden collapses or even death due to critical heart failure.

Doors in '''Level 4.4''' mostly lead to nowhere, or just an empty, bloodied room with no equipment whatsoever. At random intervals, parts of the ceiling may collapse, leaving behind debris and making navigation much more difficult. It is also important to watch for traces of [[Entity 63|predatory doors]], as they regularly manifest themselves as ordinary ones before attacking their prey. Another key to survival is to avoid barging in recklessly when encountering restricted or barricaded doors, because it is likely that someone is already in there and ready to attack a traveler at any point. Given the unpredictable nature of doors, people are advised to stay away from them completely to deter an unexpected clash from ensuing.

The walls in '''Level 4.4''' appear to be covered in various artistic depictions made out of blood. There is no confirmation as to why those are visually perceptible, but it is heavily implied that victims who either presumably succumbed to the level's hazardous nature or went insane drew all of the symbols by using limbs of the deceased to achieve this goal. This perhaps partly explains why displaced human organs can be found in every corner of '''Level 4.4''', as the bodies of those who are murdered seem to be mutilated to acquire such assets.

Interestingly, '''Level 4.4''' is filled with an abundance of lockers, most of which, however, cannot be pried or opened without keys to their corresponding padlocks. These keys are scattered across the level, usually being found in some certain rooms and unlocked drawers. Many fortunate survivors have reported being drawn to these lockers, often feeling the need to discover what is hidden beneath the surface, mainly because of the survival instinct to look for supplies or just odd curiosity in general. Further inspection indicates the disturbingly common presence of corpses stuffed inside these containers, dismembered into multiple individual parts.

Anyone who stays in '''Level 4.4''' for longer than six hours will begin to experience visual and auditory hallucinations; reflections include but are not limited to their past self, their archnemesis, and their most traumatic memories. The level's psychological effects seem to be the primary catalyst for driving these factors. If a wanderer does not retain or have any memories of the mentioned, such an event would luckily not occur. Anyone who does not have enough willpower for resistance is prone to becoming erratic and unpredictable. Eventually, they will try to kill every person present in the level. In case there is no one in sight for extended periods of time, they will turn to self-harm or even attempt to separate anatomical features from their own bodies, using any tools that are capable of doing so.
==Entities==
The only known entities that inhabit '''Level 4.4''' are [[Entity 63|predatory doors]] and [[Entity 2|windows]]. They should not be that big of an issue once one equips oneself with enough knowledge about both.
==The Black Hatred==
{{Phenomenon Class|effectiveness=4|frequency=3|danger=4}}
'''The Black Hatred''' is the main hazard of '''Level 4.4'''. Survivors of this recalled possessing high muscle tension and an extreme willingness to commit violence. As aforementioned, any beings that roam inside the level for more than six hours will face devastating mental deterioration, which, in return, contributes to the irrational actions that they may commit in the near future. Consuming large amounts of [[Object 1|almond water]] has been proven to be useful in alleviating the effects of '''The Black Hatred'''; however, this method should not be exploited, as contingencies are not entirely preventable.

Anyone who is considered "too far gone" has to be eliminated immediately lest there be any unwanted hostilities. It is recommended that long-range weapons be used to do this. If the situation is dire and necessitates immediate action, use anything available on the spot to distract or injure, thereby granting valuable time to escape from harm's way. There is currently no known cure for '''The Black Hatred''', due to it being a level-exclusive phenomenon.
==Leviathan's Curse==
{{Phenomenon Class|effectiveness=5|frequency=1|danger=5}}
'''Leviathan's Curse''' is an event that has a minuscule chance of happening within '''Level 4.4'''. During this time, all hostile individuals will be alerted to one's location. In addition, a chain of events will also be instigated in the following order:

*5 minutes in, the victim will begin receiving slight impairment, alongside a gradual increase in aggressiveness. Additionally, false delusions would begin to ramp up inside their minds, resulting in unprecedented repercussions.

*20 minutes in, '''Level 4.4''''s surface will shake violently, requiring intensive maneuvers to ensure survival. Tap water in the level at this point also gets replaced completely by blood and does not stop flowing unless one leaves the level. 

*45 minutes in, '''Level 4.4''' will alter itself significantly, transforming from a concrete building into structures of flesh webs and bones. This is the last chance for one to leave the level before it's too late.

*At exactly the 2-hour mark, '''Level 4.4''' begins to close in on ''the forsaken'', crushing them to their eternal demise. The remains left behind will be integrated into the level's structure as well. Afterwards, everything morphs back to its original form prior to the incident.
==Colonies and Outposts==
Establing a colony or outpost in '''Level 4.4''' is infeasible.
==Additional Information==
