<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Reconnaissance Report #1 - 5/23/2019</span><br>
<center><span style="font-size:17px">'''The Discovery'''</span></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
To any of the higher-ups who are reading this, we have successfully identified a new sub-level of [[Level 4]]. Initial reports suggest high sustainability rates as supplies are plentiful and can be located pretty much everywhere. Perhaps setting up an outpost would be an ideal choice for future expeditions. It’s been quite a while since we had such an opportunity, so we need to quickly seize and utilize this by all means necessary. 

On the other side, there is something a little off-putting about this place. We have sent some agents to scout around the area for any unusual sightings. What was reported back sounds shockingly unbelievable. A mortuary? Did 4.4 somehow merge with another dimension or something? There was never any information stored in the database about this particular anomaly. Again, that doesn’t matter much anyway.

On behalf of the squad leader, we would like to request additional financial and personnel support from [[Base Alpha]]. Your swift, decisive actions could help us greatly shift the future of humanity in The Backrooms.<br><br>
With regards,<br>
Hunter “Ken” Garrick.
</div></div>
<span class="mw-customtoggle-a01final mw-customtoggle-a01initial"><div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-a01initial">
<span style="color:green">'''<code>> OPEN FILE #0A-2?</code>'''</span></div></span> <div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-a01final"> <div class="mw-customtoggle-a01final mw-customtoggle-a01initial"> <span style="color:green">'''<code>> CLOSE FILE #0A-2</code>'''</span></div> </div> <div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-a01final">
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Incident Report #2 - 8/8/2021</span><br>
<center><span style="font-size:17px">'''Dissolution'''</span></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
A group consisting of 50 unidentified individuals seemingly made their way into '''Level 4.4''' and were spotted heading straight for the administrative office, where various officials were operating. Security forces managed to intercept a series of messages from one of their leaders, thereby concluding that it was an attempted coup by anarchists wanting to take over the entire place completely. Despite this, bravery and intelligence couldn’t stop the vicious attack from taking place.

What’s left of 4.4 now can be best described as a bloodbath. The extreme part is these people didn’t just kill using any conventional methods. They use axes, medieval-like weapons, chainsaws, and even suicide bombers to do the bidding. After being under siege for approximately 52 hours, the attack was repelled thanks to the external help from other groups and many unspecified wanderers.

Nevertheless, public opinion didn’t go the way we wanted it to. After a classified memo was leaked, stating that some of the bigwigs may have had some role in assisting the rioters, it eroded completely. People grew so insecure that whenever somebody did something they deemed shady or suspicious, a murder case would certainly be “an option on the menu." 

Plans for total evacuation are currently on the way, and we are working tirelessly to make sure a serious leadership misconduct like this never goes unaddressed again.
</div></div>
==Addendum==
<div style="text-align: center; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0); border: double 4.5px white; padding: 10px;"><center><big><big>'''''Record 0A-3:'''''</big></big>
"Promise"
</center>
----I’ve been working as a prison warden for like 3 years. It isn't so fun, and I was hella lucky to even be able to achieve this position. Every day, I meet criminals from all across the spectrum. Some seem despicable, whereas some have quite, let’s say, tragic backstories. It’s been wearing me down a bit emotionally, but the work kind of enlightens me on whether these people still have some sense of conscience or not, which is a good thing. I can maybe dive deeper into their character and whatever values they might cherish, if those things even exist.<br><br>

Two months ago, there was this new inmate from Los Angeles (California). He was brought to this place during a confinement transfer from the Metropolitan Detention Center to here. Apparently, from what I’ve heard of and read about, he was responsible for thirty-eight counts of murder, three counts of arson, and six counts of the destruction of public and private property. Technically speaking, he has, of course, obstructed the administration of justice. Now, he’s just sitting there waiting for the death penalty to be carried out.

I’ve gone through his cell a couple of times too. He seemed to be lost and perturbed, to be frank. A young man with an entire life ahead of him yet chose to follow the hollow path, removing all restrictions between right and wrong. During a routine check, he asked me if I could do him a favor, to which I replied, “Sure.” He then held up a big piece of paper and requested that I deliver it to his dad. I was a bit reluctant at first but went along with it either way. I was originally intending to see what it was all about, then figured it would be morally wrong to do such a thing.

Some days after the execution, I went to his still grieving family’s house and did what I had to do. I felt so relieved after that. It was probably the first and only time I agreed to help a criminal out. Let’s just pray that humans stop being so evil to each other for once before it’s too late.
{{Note|body=<span style="color:red;">
<center>''A Reminder''</center><br>
Hey, Dad. It’s your son, Jack. Just want to let you fellas know that I’m on death row and will be gone from this miserable world soon. I write this mainly to vent my frustrations to you, and I do hope this time you’ll actually take some of these to heart instead of brushing everything off like before.

I thought we were going to be a normal family, no? I was humiliated at school every single day, and with your typical ignorance, which is nothing new at this point, you vaguely told me to “get over it” or “It can’t be that bad." How did that help at all??? You do realize that the journey to adulthood for us teenagers was very volatile, right? The last thing a child would like to witness is for their parents to invalidate their feelings like a non-issue.

I constantly went home feeling like dogshit, and what did you do about it? Ranting about how your generation had it worse than we did? That’s quite pathetic, not gonna lie. If you were one of us, you’d probably understand how the world operates better. You pushed me to yield a perfectionist mindset, and how did that work out, I wonder? Four visits to a mental hospital and being treated like a psycho? Hope THAT was worth it.

Genuine question: Did you ever feel bad for all you’d done to us? Just because your little “business enterprise” wasn’t sailing the way you wanted it to go didn’t automatically give you the right to take your anger out on us. Remember that one time you almost beat Mom to death, and I begged the SHIT out of you to stop? Clearly your impulses far overwhelmed rational judgment more than it seemed they did.

Thanks to you, I learned that violence should be the answer to anything out of my control. The candlelight that defined compassion and empathy inside me was probably beyond extinguished by that point. Although I clearly acknowledge I am in the wrong here, it’s just merely a manifestation of your character inside me. Had you not pushed me to the edge so many times, perhaps all of these could have been avoided.

My time is running thin, so that’s the end, I guess. I hope you consider this letter seriously. It’s not too late for redemption. I didn’t report you to the authorities simply because I loved you. Don’t make the same atrocious mistakes that I did. I may still have doubts about you, though; in the end, I am still your son, and that matters more than anything this cruel world could ever offer you.

Farewell, may we see each other again in the afterlife.</span>
}}
